metadata.title: Evektor SportStar
aws::graph::propositions: # Evektor SportStar Technical Specifications
Evektor SportStar has a wing loading of 6 kg/m2 (11.6 lb/sq ft).
Evektor SportStar has a power-to-mass ratio of 0.128 kW/kg (0.078 hp/lb).
Evektor SportStar requires a take-off run of 190 m (623 ft).
Evektor SportStar requires a take-off distance to 15 m (49 ft) height of 365 m (1,198 ft).
Evektor SportStar requires a landing run of 180 m (591 ft).
Evektor SportStar is equipped with Garmin G3X avionics.
Evektor SportStar has a 10.6" Primary Flight Display (GDU 460).
Evektor SportStar has a 10.6" Multi Function Display (GDU 460).
Evektor SportStar has two Air Data and Attitude and Heading Reference Systems (GSU 25).
Evektor SportStar is equipped with a Magnetometer (GMU 22).
Evektor SportStar has an Engine Monitoring System (GEA 24).
Evektor SportStar has an Outside Air Temperature sensor (GTP 59).
Evektor SportStar is equipped with GPS antennas.
Evektor SportStar has Synthetic Vision capability.
Evektor SportStar has a backup battery.
Evektor SportStar has a back-up Air speed indicator and Altimeter (diameter 2 ¼").
Evektor SportStar is equipped with a COMM Garmin GTR225A radio.
Evektor SportStar is equipped with a Transponder GTX328 (mode S).
Evektor SportStar is equipped with an ACK A-30 emergency locator transmitter.
Evektor SportStar has a SIRS compass.

text:
6 kg/m2 (11.6 lb/sq ft)
Power/mass: 0.128 kW/kg (0.078 hp/lb)
Take-off run: 190 m (623 ft)
Take-off distance to 15 m (49 ft): 365 m (1,198 ft)
Landing run: 180 m (591 ft)
Avionics

Garmin G3X fit

10.6" PFD - Primary Flight Display (GDU 460)
10.6" MFD - Multi Function Display (GDU 460)
2 ADAHRS - Air Data and Attitude and Heading Reference System (GSU 25)
Magnetometer (GMU 22)
EMS (GEA 24)
OAT sensor (GTP 59)
GPS antenas, Synthetic Vision, backup battery
Back-up Air speed indicator + Altimeter (dia 2 ¼")
COMM Garmin GTR225A + Transponder GTX328 (mode S) + ACK A-30
Compass SIRS
